## Harness Simplification

Regularly review one harness component. Keep it when it prevents repeated
failures. Remove or merge it when it adds upkeep without improving
verification, restartability, or scope control.

Run an ablation when validating a component's value: snapshot the benchmark
evidence above, remove one component, rerun the same task set, and keep it
removed when grades and completion do not drop. Log each ablation as a row in
the benchmark table above.

Structural harness scores do not prove real agent effectiveness. Record
representative before/after agent-session evidence or benchmark notes before
making release claims about agent reliability.
